twips.name: twips
twips.description: Twentieths of a point (equivalent to 1/1440th of an inch).

DocumentElement.name: DocumentElement
DocumentElement.description: Any valid element which can be added to the document structure.

StyleType.name: StyleType
StyleType.description: The style type used for the document element.

BorderType.name: BorderType
BorderType.description:
A border type which will be added to the document element.

  • "none" - no border will be added to the created element or the selected element side.
  • "single" - a single border will be added to the created element or the selected element side.

ShdType.name: ShdType
ShdType.description: A shade type which can be added to the document element.

pt_8.name: pt_8
pt_8.description: Eighths of a point (24 eighths of a point = 3 points).

HdrFtrType.name: HdrFtrType
HdrFtrType.description:
Header and footer types which can be applied to the document sections.

  • "default" - a header or footer which can be applied to any default page.
  • "title" - a header or footer which is applied to the title page.
  • "even" - a header or footer which can be applied to even pages to distinguish them from the odd ones (which will be considered default).

TableWidth.name: TableWidth
TableWidth.description:
The possible values for the units of the width property are defined by a specific table or table cell width property.

  • "auto" - sets the table or table cell width to auto width.
  • "twips" - sets the table or table cell width to be measured in twentieths of a point.
  • "nul" - sets the table or table cell width to be of a zero value.
  • "percent" - sets the table or table cell width to be measured in percent to the parent container.

TableStyleOverrideType.name: TableStyleOverrideType
TableStyleOverrideType.description:
This simple type specifies possible values for the table sections to which the current conditional formatting properties will be applied when this selected table style is used.

  • "topLeftCell" - specifies that the table formatting is applied to the top left cell.
  • "topRightCell" - specifies that the table formatting is applied to the top right cell.
  • "bottomLeftCell" - specifies that the table formatting is applied to the bottom left cell.
  • "bottomRightCell" - specifies that the table formatting is applied to the bottom right cell.
  • "firstRow" - specifies that the table formatting is applied to the first row.
  • "lastRow" - specifies that the table formatting is applied to the last row.
  • "firstColumn" - specifies that the table formatting is applied to the first column. Any subsequent row which is in table header ({@link ApiTableRowPr#SetTableHeader}) will also use this conditional format.
  • "lastColumn" - specifies that the table formatting is applied to the last column.
  • "bandedColumn" - specifies that the table formatting is applied to odd numbered groupings of rows.
  • "bandedColumnEven" - specifies that the table formatting is applied to even numbered groupings of rows.
  • "bandedRow" - specifies that the table formatting is applied to odd numbered groupings of columns.
  • "bandedRowEven" - specifies that the table formatting is applied to even numbered groupings of columns.
  • "wholeTable" - specifies that the conditional formatting is applied to the whole table.

ParagraphContent.name: ParagraphContent
ParagraphContent.description: The types of elements that can be added to the paragraph structure.

RelFromH.name: RelFromH
RelFromH.description: The possible values for the base which the relative horizontal positioning of an object will be calculated from.

RelFromV.name: RelFromV
RelFromV.description: The possible values for the base which the relative vertical positioning of an object will be calculated from.

EMU.name: EMU
EMU.description: English measure unit. 1 mm = 36000 EMUs, 1 inch = 914400 EMUs.

ShapeType.name: ShapeType
ShapeType.description: This type specifies the preset shape geometry that will be used for a shape.

ChartType.name: ChartType
ChartType.description: This type specifies the available chart types which can be used to create a new chart.

VerticalTextAlign.name: VerticalTextAlign
VerticalTextAlign.description: The available text vertical alignment (used to align text in a shape with a placement for text inside it).

TickLabelPosition.name: TickLabelPosition
TickLabelPosition.description:
Possible values for the position of chart tick labels (either horizontal or vertical).

  • "none" - not display the selected tick labels.
  • "nextTo" - sets the position of the selected tick labels next to the main label.
  • "low" - sets the position of the selected tick labels in the part of the chart with lower values.
  • "high" - sets the position of the selected tick labels in the part of the chart with higher values.

BlipFillType.name: BlipFillType
BlipFillType.description:
The type of a fill which uses an image as a background.

  • "tile" - if the image is smaller than the shape which is filled, the image will be tiled all over the created shape surface.
  • "stretch" - if the image is smaller than the shape which is filled, the image will be stretched to fit the created shape surface.

PatternType.name: PatternType
PatternType.description: The available preset patterns which can be used for the fill.

SdtLock.name: SdtLock
SdtLock.description: The lock type of the content control.

ScaleFlag.name: ScaleFlag
ScaleFlag.description: The condition to scale an image in the picture form.

numberedRefTo.name: numberedRefTo
numberedRefTo.description:
Available values of the "numbered" reference type:

  • "pageNum" - the numbered item page number;
  • "paraNum" - the numbered item paragraph number;
  • "noCtxParaNum" - the abbreviated paragraph number (the specific item only, e.g. instead of "4.1.1" you refer to "1" only);
  • "fullCtxParaNum" - the full paragraph number, e.g. "4.1.1";
  • "text" - the paragraph text value, e.g. if you have "4.1.1. Terms and Conditions", you refer to "Terms and Conditions" only;
  • "aboveBelow" - the words "above" or "below" depending on the item position.

headingRefTo.name: headingRefTo
headingRefTo.description:
Available values of the "heading" reference type:

  • "text" - the entire heading text;
  • "pageNum" - the heading page number;
  • "headingNum" - the heading sequence number;
  • "noCtxHeadingNum" - the abbreviated heading number. Make sure the cursor pointer is in the section you are referencing to, e.g. you are in section 4 and you wish to refer to heading 4.B, so instead of "4.B" you receive "B" only;
  • "fullCtxHeadingNum" - the full heading number even if the cursor pointer is in the same section;
  • "aboveBelow" - the words "above" or "below" depending on the item position.

bookmarkRefTo.name: bookmarkRefTo
bookmarkRefTo.description:
Available values of the "bookmark" reference type:

  • "text" - the entire bookmark text;
  • "pageNum" - the bookmark page number;
  • "paraNum" - the bookmark paragraph number;
  • "noCtxParaNum" - the abbreviated paragraph number (the specific item only, e.g. instead of "4.1.1" you refer to "1" only);
  • "fullCtxParaNum - the full paragraph number, e.g. "4.1.1";
  • "aboveBelow" - the words "above" or "below" depending on the item position.

footnoteRefTo.name: footnoteRefTo
footnoteRefTo.description:
Available values of the "footnote" reference type:

  • "footnoteNum" - the footnote number;
  • "pageNum" - the page number of the footnote;
  • "aboveBelow" - the words "above" or "below" depending on the position of the item;
  • "formFootnoteNum" - the form number formatted as a footnote. The numbering of the actual footnotes is not affected.

endnoteRefTo.name: endnoteRefTo
endnoteRefTo.description:
Available values of the "endnote" reference type:

  • "endnoteNum" - the endnote number;
  • "pageNum" - the endnote page number;
  • "aboveBelow" - the words "above" or "below" depending on the item position;
  • "formEndnoteNum" - the form number formatted as an endnote. The numbering of the actual endnotes is not affected.

captionRefTo.name: captionRefTo
captionRefTo.description:
Available values of the "equation"/"figure"/"table" reference type:

  • "entireCaption"- the entire caption text;
  • "labelNumber" - the label and object number only, e.g. "Table 1.1";
  • "captionText" - the caption text only;
  • "pageNum" - the page number containing the referenced object;
  • "aboveBelow" - the words "above" or "below" depending on the item position.

CaptionNumberingFormat.name: CaptionNumberingFormat
CaptionNumberingFormat.description:
Possible values for the caption numbering format.

  • "ALPHABETIC" - upper letter.
  • "alphabetic" - lower letter.
  • "Roman" - upper Roman.
  • "roman" - lower Roman.
  • "Arabic" - arabic.

CaptionSep.name: CaptionSep
CaptionSep.description:
Possible values for the caption separator.

  • "hyphen" - the "-" punctuation mark.
  • "period" - the "." punctuation mark.
  • "colon" - the ":" punctuation mark.
  • "longDash" - the "—" punctuation mark.
  • "dash" - the "-" punctuation mark.

properties.name: ShowPageNums
properties.description: Specifies whether to show page numbers in the table of contents.

properties.name: RightAlgn
properties.description: Specifies whether to right-align page numbers in the table of contents.

properties.name: LeaderType
properties.description: The leader type in the table of contents.

properties.name: FormatAsLinks
properties.description: Specifies whether to format the table of contents as links.

properties.name: BuildFrom
properties.description: Specifies whether to generate the table of contents from the outline levels or the specified styles.

properties.name: TocStyle
properties.description: The table of contents style type.

properties.name: ShowPageNums
properties.description: Specifies whether to show page numbers in the table of figures.

properties.name: RightAlgn
properties.description: Specifies whether to right-align page numbers in the table of figures.

properties.name: LeaderType
properties.description: The leader type in the table of figures.

properties.name: FormatAsLinks
properties.description: Specifies whether to format the table of figures as links.

properties.name: BuildFrom
properties.description: Specifies whether to generate the table of figures based on the specified caption label or the paragraph style name used (for example, "Heading 1").

properties.name: LabelNumber
properties.description: Specifies whether to include the label and number in the table of figures.

properties.name: TofStyle
properties.description: The table of figures style type.

TocBuildFromPr.name: TocBuildFromPr
TocBuildFromPr.description: Table of contents properties which specify whether to generate the table of contents from the outline levels or the specified styles.

properties.name: OutlineLvls
properties.description: Maximum number of levels in the table of contents.

properties.name: StylesLvls
properties.description: Style levels (for example, [{Name: "Heading 1", Lvl: 2}, {Name: "Heading 2", Lvl: 3}]). If StylesLvls.length > 0, then the OutlineLvls property will be ignored.

properties.name: Name
properties.description: Style name (for example, "Heading 1").

properties.name: Lvl
properties.description: Level which will be applied to the specified style in the table of contents.

TocLeader.name: TocLeader
TocLeader.description:
Possible values for the table of contents leader:

  • "dot" - "......."
  • "dash" - "-------"
  • "underline" - "_______"

TocStyle.name: TocStyle
TocStyle.description: Possible values for the table of contents style.

TofStyle.name: TofStyle
TofStyle.description: Possible values for the table of figures style.

properties.name: IsAnswer
properties.description: Specifies whether this is an initial comment or a reply to another comment.

properties.name: CommentMessage
properties.description: The text of the current comment.

properties.name: Date
properties.description: The time when this change was made in local time.

properties.name: DateUTC
properties.description: The time when this change was made in UTC.

properties.name: QuoteText
properties.description: The text to which this comment is related.

CommentReport.name: CommentReport
CommentReport.description: Report on all comments. This is a dictionary where the keys are usernames.

properties.name: Type
properties.description: Review record type.

properties.name: Value
properties.description: Review change value that is set for the "TextAdd" and "TextRem" types only.

properties.name: Date
properties.description: The time when this change was made.

ReviewReport.name: ReviewReport
ReviewReport.description: Report on all review changes. This is a dictionary where the keys are usernames.
